text: Drita Islami (born 1 August 1996) is a Macedonian hurdler. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's 400 metres hurdles race; her time of 1:01.18 in the heats did not qualify her for the semifinals. Drita Islami is at the same time national record holder of North Macedonia at 400 metres hurdles. ==References== Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Macedonian female athletes Category:Olympic athletes of North Macedonia Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Albanians in North Macedonia Category:European Games competitors for North Macedonia Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2015 European Games Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2018 Mediterranean Games
